  "text": "In this section, we will prove Theorem 1.6. To establish the theorem for polynomial linear statistics φ, a proof will be given that follows a similar tract to the analogous statement proven for the Laguerre and Hermite ensembles in [CITATION_1] . The key to this method of proof is establishing a certain palindromy. Recall that a polynomial p(z) = a n z n + a n−1 z n−1 + · · ·+ a 1 z + a 0 is palindromic in z if a n z n + a n−1 z n−1 + · · ·+ a 1 z + a 0 = a 0 z n + a 1 z n−1 + · · · + a n−1 z + a n , or equivalently that p(z) = z n p(z −1 ).",
